msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/basics.performant_code.rst:447
msgid "joblib"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/basics.performant_code.rst:450
msgid ""
"``joblib`` is a library that provides helper functions which make it easy to "
"parallelize tasks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/basics.performant_code.rst:453
msgid "For example,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/basics.performant_code.rst:455
msgid ""
"``joblib``'s default backend ``loky`` relies on `cloudpickle <https://github."
"com/cloudpipe/cloudpickle>`__ for serialization and can handle a wider range "
"of Python objects than the standard ``pickle`` module. (e.g., lambda "
"functions)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/basics.performant_code.rst:459
msgid ""
"`joblib.cpu_count() <https://joblib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/generated/"
"joblib.cpu_count.html>`__ returns the number of CPUs available to the "
"current process, taking into account constraints such as CPU affinity "
"settings and Linux CFS scheduler quotas. This may provide a more accurate "
"value than `os.cpu_count` and `os.process_cpu_count <https://docs.python."
"org/3/library/os.html#os.process_cpu_count>`__ functions in Docker "
"containers and other resource-constrained environments."
msgstr ""

